54
00:04:57,790 --> 00:05:04,330
Por favor, tómense un tiempo para
colocarse en una postura cómoda.

55
00:05:09,270 --> 00:05:13,650
Pueden usar la asistencia de almohadones,
pillas.

56
00:05:21,410 --> 00:05:26,770
Tomando un asana que puedan mantener por
tres a cinco minutos.

57
00:05:26,830 --> 00:05:33,850
Of course, you're welcome to move as
needed, but there is value in coming to

58
00:05:33,850 --> 00:05:34,530
stillness.

59
00:05:35,610 --> 00:05:41,610
Obviamente están invitados a moverse si lo
necesitan, pero es una invitación a la

60
00:05:41,610 --> 00:05:43,170
quietud, a mantenerla.

61
00:05:44,170 --> 00:05:50,390
Continue to arrange your body so that the
spine is comfortably upright.

62
00:05:57,610 --> 00:06:02,510
The shoulders and arms in a relaxed
position.

63
00:06:07,410 --> 00:06:11,570
With the hands in a mudra or gesture of
your choice.

64
00:06:15,770 --> 00:06:23,890
A simple one is to touch the tip of the
thumb to the first index finger.

65
00:06:29,130 --> 00:06:31,810
With the palms up or down.

66
00:06:35,430 --> 00:06:37,190
Resting on the knees or thighs.

67
00:06:41,690 --> 00:06:46,150
The neck and head in alignment with the
lower spine.

68
00:06:51,410 --> 00:06:57,610
Bring your awareness into your whole body
and really feel for the balance between

69
00:06:57,610 --> 00:06:59,230
left and right sides.

70
00:06:59,230 --> 00:07:05,870
Trae tu atención a todo el cuerpo y busca
el equilibrio entre tu lado derecho y tu

71
00:07:05,870 --> 00:07:06,460
lado izquierdo.

72
00:07:12,170 --> 00:07:17,230
Sentí esto en los pies, rodillas,
en los espiones.

73
00:07:18,270 --> 00:07:24,310
Feel for that balance in the torso,
the shoulders, the neck and head.

74
00:07:30,770 --> 00:07:36,170
Make any subtle adjustments to bring
yourself closer to physical balance if

75
00:07:36,170 --> 00:07:36,610
required.

76
00:07:36,610 --> 00:07:44,150
Y puedes hacer los ajustes necesarios para
traerte más cerca del equilibrio entre

77
00:07:44,150 --> 00:07:44,790
ambos lados.

78
00:07:49,520 --> 00:07:55,200
Once you have found some stillness,
start to focus on the movement of the

79
00:07:55,200 --> 00:07:55,540
breath.

80
00:07:55,860 --> 00:08:01,980
Una vez que hayas alcanzado cierta
quietud, focalizate en el movimiento de la

81
00:08:01,980 --> 00:08:02,720
respiración.

82
00:08:03,720 --> 00:08:11,240
Without changing it by force, just read
it, the quality of it at this time of the

83
00:08:11,240 --> 00:08:12,000
day.

84
00:08:24,020 --> 00:08:29,520
If it in any way reflects the activities
of the day.

85
00:08:36,200 --> 00:08:42,320
And if any impressions of the day are
moving through the mind or the emotions.

86
00:08:49,640 --> 00:08:53,460
Consider neither feeding them nor
resisting them.

87
00:08:58,900 --> 00:09:05,800
Letting them move through you like clouds
and preferring to focus on the breath.

88
00:09:14,040 --> 00:09:20,440
Begin to deepen the breath in both
directions gradually, progressively.

89
00:09:30,580 --> 00:09:36,780
So that over a number of breaths,
you find that you are exhaling more

90
00:09:36,780 --> 00:09:39,900
completely and inhaling more fully.

91
00:10:13,870 --> 00:10:17,850
Add to this more complete breath a mental
exercise.

92
00:10:19,250 --> 00:10:24,810
Agregale a esta respiración más completa
un foco mental.

93
00:10:28,870 --> 00:10:31,350
El pasaje psíquico frontal.

94
00:10:37,470 --> 00:10:44,270
Una línea imaginaria o tubo en la parte
frontal del torso.

95
00:10:49,790 --> 00:10:55,650
Que va desde el ombligo a través del
esternón hasta el agujerito de la

96
00:10:55,650 --> 00:10:56,140
garganta.

97
00:11:05,720 --> 00:11:13,310
A medida que inhalas, guías respiración
por ese tubo hasta la garganta.

98
00:11:20,010 --> 00:11:27,130
Y en la exhalación, guía la respiración
hacia abajo hasta el ombligo.

99
00:11:27,610 --> 00:11:36,430
Si no viaja por ese camino, no hay
problema.

100
00:11:42,370 --> 00:11:47,770
Continúa enfocando tu mente en la
respiración de una manera gentil.

101
00:12:01,570 --> 00:12:17,470
Con la próxima inhalación, continúa
pasando la garganta hasta el entrefejo.

102
00:12:21,850 --> 00:12:25,710
Mantén tu atención en ese punto,
brumadilla.

103
00:12:33,130 --> 00:12:38,750
Incluso los ojos pueden volverse hacia
adentro y ligeramente hacia arriba,

104
00:12:39,290 --> 00:12:41,370
mirando desde adentro.

105
00:12:48,570 --> 00:12:53,010
Imagina que estás mirando la llama en una
vela.

106
00:12:54,370 --> 00:12:58,750
A veces la imagen aparece, a veces no.

107
00:13:09,130 --> 00:13:14,730
Siempre puedes dibujar la silueta o la
forma de la llama.

108
00:13:15,830 --> 00:13:20,190
Imagina el color o la forma de la llama
que tienes.

109
00:13:23,010 --> 00:13:25,290
De una vela que tú realmente tienes.

110
00:13:35,130 --> 00:13:42,510
Imagínate que esta llama representa el
conocimiento intuitivo disponible dentro

111
00:13:42,510 --> 00:13:43,010
nuestro.

112
00:13:47,050 --> 00:13:49,750
Siempre disponible si miramos hacia
adentro.

113
00:13:53,010 --> 00:13:57,710
Mantra Om tres veces juntos, seguido por
los Shanti Mantras.

114
00:14:03,850 --> 00:14:09,350
Si sabes los mantras, estás bienvenido a
cantar conmigo o simplemente a escuchar.

115
00:14:16,550 --> 00:14:22,990
Respira lento y profundo para cantar el
mantra Om.

116
00:14:23,010 --> 00:14:24,070
Mantra Om

117
00:14:28,710 --> 00:14:30,110
Mantra Om

118
00:14:34,470 --> 00:14:43,990
Mantra Om Mantra Om

119
00:15:05,800 --> 00:15:15,540
Mantra Om

120
00:15:37,040 --> 00:15:40,880
Sit for just a few more moments in
