220
00:29:47,970 --> 00:29:53,590
Y para los que han estado estudiando yoga
e integrándola en sus vidas,

221
00:29:59,650 --> 00:30:04,850
realmente les recomiendo que vayan
entrando en algunos términos sánscritos.

222
00:30:04,850 --> 00:30:11,910
This year in particular I have started to
do that with mantras and chants and it's a

223
00:30:11,910 --> 00:30:13,330
whole new dimension.

224
00:30:20,910 --> 00:30:28,390
The cultures that have used Sanskrit for
spirituality put a lot of effort to

225
00:30:28,390 --> 00:30:31,350
accurately describe what they're talking
about.

226
00:30:35,430 --> 00:30:38,110
Han hecho un esfuerzo de hacerlo muy
preciso.

227
00:30:40,270 --> 00:30:44,570
The physical body is called annamayakosha.

228
00:30:44,930 --> 00:30:47,910
El cuerpo físico se llama annamayakosha.

229
00:30:49,190 --> 00:30:52,910
So all of these have mayakosha after them.

230
00:30:53,670 --> 00:30:56,650
Todos tienen mayakosha como terminación.

231
00:30:57,550 --> 00:31:01,050
So anna means food.

232
00:31:02,430 --> 00:31:03,890
Anna significa comida.

233
00:31:04,330 --> 00:31:10,250
So the physical body is made up of food,
